==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Puberty
<hw>Pu"ber*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pubertas</ets>, fr. <ets>puber</ets>, <ets>pubes</ets>, adult: cf.
F. <ets>pubert⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The earliest age
at which persons are capable of begetting or bearing children, usually
considered, in temperate climates, to be about fourteen years in males
and twelve in females.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The period when a plant first
bears flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puberulent</ent>⟦br⟧
